00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:48.000
 and kind of went through what it is, what the sections of the practice are

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:53.000
 and so we were thinking to just continue with that pattern

00:26:53.000 --> 00:26:58.000
 as we're cycling through week to week with this

00:26:58.000 --> 00:27:06.000
 and so last week was maybe almost a blur as to what we did and went over

00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:11.000
 but we'll just start in the beginning and we'll move our way through

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:17.000
 so we thought today would be kind of again setting up the circumstances

00:27:17.000 --> 00:27:22.000
 for our practice looking at what are called the three frames

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:26.000
 or the three noble ones and then also with our nundra in particular

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:30.000
 to some degree start to look at the sections of nundra

00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:34.000
 like we mentioned there's many nundra practices

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:41.000
 and nundra means foundation, what goes before or what's the essence

00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:50.000
 the source, the heart of any and all truly beneficial practice

00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:54.000
 nundra has all those elements and so we'll go over those sections

00:27:54.000 --> 00:28:00.000
 basically there's two nundras, there's outer nundra or kind of common nundra

00:28:00.000 --> 00:28:04.000
 common foundational things to take into our mind and heart

00:28:04.000 --> 00:28:13.000
 and then the uncommon extraordinary nundra of the practices in particular

00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:17.000
 and so we'll go over those as the weeks go

00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:21.000
 a few people had asked about especially the mandala section

00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:25.000
 so we will go over that, I'll send out an email

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:32.000
 which kind of will have a little bit of a schedule as to when we can focus more on certain topics

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:38.000
 but first we have the outer nundra, four thoughts that turn the mind

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:43.000
 and then once we enter the extraordinary nundra

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:56.000
 we have taking refuge, bodhicitta, mandala offering, vajrasattva practice, purification, guru yoga

00:28:56.000 --> 00:29:02.000
 and then in addition to that we have this aspiration to Amitabha to accomplish PoA

00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:08.000
 as well as the charity of giving everything with our great bodhicitta

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:14.000
 and so we'll send out a little bit of a schedule as to looking at the Saturdays we'll be doing that

00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:20.000
 so people can kind of have some sense of how we're progressing

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:41.000
 so with the practice, practice or meditation means we're becoming familiar

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:44.000
 familiarizing with things as they are

00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:52.000
 the Great Kindness Buddha Shakyamuni gave the profound vast ocean of teachings

00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:58.000
 that so beautifully through the blessings of the lineage of this lineage of practice and study

00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:06.000
 which came to Tibet in the 8th century entails the full package of the Buddhist teachings

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:13.000
 which can be summarized into three vehicles or three yanas that are practiced as a unity

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:27.000
 the whole aim of the Buddhist teachings are to remove our obscurations and the causes of them

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:33.000
 and by that naturally bringing out our innate goodness qualities

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:39.000
 our innate Buddhahood central to the teachings is that the Buddha taught

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:44.000
 every single living being has a Buddha nature

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:57.000
 has that potential for inconceivable, uncompounded, immeasurable love, wisdom, compassion

00:30:57.000 --> 00:31:02.000
 qualities we all have but just need to bring out

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:11.000
 and so by seeing, refraining from harm, engaging in benefit

00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:16.000
 working with our own mind is our path and our practice

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:20.000
 and like we'll get to a little bit later on

00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:28.000
 all the results of our experience have their causes

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:38.000
 so in the really big big big picture the cause of our Buddhahood is our Buddha nature

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:42.000
 so that's something definitely to take in our mind and our heart

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:45.000
 and that's what we're doing with the teachings

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:49.000
 and so we have, we're developing our wisdom

00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:54.000
 we have what are called the three wisdoms

00:31:54.000 --> 00:32:02.000
 which are listening, hearing, reading, the teachings

00:32:02.000 --> 00:32:10.000
 and then contemplating, thinking, reflecting, taking them to heart with practice

00:32:10.000 --> 00:32:16.000
 so study, contemplation, practice

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:26.000
 and similarly when we begin any practice or maybe take a step back

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:35.000
 we have our practice time to kind of bring in that third wisdom

00:32:35.000 --> 00:32:39.000
 with these sessions we're kind of moving a little bit

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:43.000
 with all of those developing those three wisdoms

00:32:43.000 --> 00:32:49.000
 but what little bit I bring up here now obviously isn't the whole vast ocean of the Dharma

00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:55.000
 but little sparks and this is really like Rinpoche mentions and it's true

00:32:55.000 --> 00:33:00.000
 we've all heard so many teachings, we've all done some degree of practice

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:04.000
 just bringing them up into our own minds and hearts

00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:08.000
 and settling into the practice, working with our own mind

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:12.000
 is what we're really trying to do

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:18.000
 and so when we have a formal practice that we're taking

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:25.000
 there's what are called three frames or three noble ones

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:32.000
 which is essentially saying we want to kind of have the right frame

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:37.000
 the right vessel for our practice to touch home base

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:44.000
 and then everything in the world has a beginning, has a middle and has an end

00:33:44.000 --> 00:33:49.000
 and so kind of using that natural truth

00:33:49.000 --> 00:33:54.000
 we're working with that with how we structure our practice

00:33:54.000 --> 00:34:04.000
 and everything that's said in the teachings, everything that happens is circumstantial

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:09.000
 our motivation is what makes all the difference

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:14.000
 and so like Rinpoche says at the beginning of every teaching

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:18.000
 like all the great masters say at the beginning of every teaching

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:24.000
 but this is something we should always be doing with every time we sit down to practice

00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:32.000
 is engaging with what's called the three motivations

00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:38.000
 motivation, intention really makes all the difference

00:34:38.000 --> 00:34:43.000
 and so that's the big part of this first frame

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:47.000
 and again they're not like a step we're going to take and leave it behind

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:52.000
 we're setting the foundations and we're growing from there

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:56.000
 so when we have made a little bit of time for practice

00:34:56.000 --> 00:35:01.000
 we want to sit down, we want to reconnect with those

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:06.000
 and so basically like we've heard many times but again we need to do it

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:13.000
 it's connecting with our joy, our appreciation

00:35:13.000 --> 00:35:26.000
 relax, you know, let go and recognize just how precious our situation is

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:34.000
 quietly, calmly, it doesn't have to be like some panic

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:42.000
 excitement but just take a moment to refresh and reflect on how precious our situation is

00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:47.000
 and then engaging our bodhicitta

